==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[#Latin|phimosis]]'', from Greek ''[[φίμωσις]]'' ‘muzzling’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/faɪˈməʊsɪs/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|phimoses}}

# (''Medicine'') A contraction of the [[foreskin]] (either as a stage of development or a pathological condition), which prevents it from being retracted.
#:*'''1762''': ’Twill end in a '''''phimosis''''', replied Dr. ''Slop''. — Laurence Sterne, ''The Life & Opinions of Tristram Shandy, Gentleman'' (Penguin 2003, p. 361)